HEADWORD: Diuturnal
<hw>Di`u*tur"nal</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>diuturnus</ets>, fr. <ets>diu</ets> a long time, by day; akin to
<ets>dies</ets> day.]</ety> <def>Of long continuance; lasting.</def>
